title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender; drain.
Mix with remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with paprika, if desired.

title: pea salad
directions: In bowl, mix peas, onion, celery and pepper.
In serving bowl, place lettuce to cover bottom.
Place 1/2 the pea mixture on top of lettuce; sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over that.
Cover with another layer of lettuce pieces,
then rest of pea mixture. Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over top.
Empty mayonnaise on top and spread evenly.
Place cheese on top of mayonnaise, covering it evenly.
Empty bacon bits on cheese and spread evenly.
Decorate with celery leaf, if desired.

title: pasta chicken
directions: Cook pasta; set aside.
Cut up chicken; stir-fry with some garlic and parsley.
Mix together the milk, bouillon, cornstarch and margarine; add to chicken.
Pour over pasta.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix together and press into oblong pan all but chocolate chips.
Melt chips and pour over other mixture; spread evenly. Let cool and cut into squares.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine and pour into buttered casserole dish. Bake 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Lay chicken in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cheese on top.
Mix soup with 1/2 can water; cover chicken.
Mix stuffing with butter and water according to package directions.
Place on top of casserole and cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: zesta steak
directions: Cut beef in 8 pieces.
Combine flour, cracker crumbs, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix egg and Worcestershire sauce together.
Dip steak into egg and Worcestershire sauce mixture, then in crumbs mixture.
Fry in skillet in oil, then place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and put on onion slices.
Combine tomato sauce, chili sauce, brown sugar, chili powder, dry mustard and vinegar.
Pour over steak.
Put on green pepper slices (on top). Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: honey-lime chicken
directions: Mix mustard, lime juice, garlic, soy sauce and lime peel until well blended.
Reserve 1/2 cup of the mustard mixture for serving with cooked chicken.
Grill or broil chicken 15 minutes or until cooked through, turning and brushing occasionally with remaining mustard mixture.
Serve with reserved 1/2 cup mustard mixture.

title: tasty snack
directions: Mix together in a bowl. Spread out on waxed paper to harden.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, corn
syrup
and
water over low heat until sugar is	dissolved.
Cook
without
stirring
until
a
small amount of mixture dropped into cold water forms a hard ball or the candy thermometer
reads	260°.
In
mixing
bowl beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Continue beating while pouring hot syrup in a thin stream into egg whites.
Add vanilla; beat until mixture holds its shape and becomes slightly dull.	Fold in nuts.
Drop mixture
from tip of buttered spoon onto waxed paper.
Four dozen is this recipe's yield.

title: armenian pilaf
directions: Melt butter in heavy pan.
Break vermicelli into small pieces; saute in butter until golden brown, stirring constantly.
Add rice; keep stirring until rice is well coated, 2 to 3 minutes. Add boiling chicken broth and salt.
Cook, covered, on medium-low heat for 20 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with fork. Serves 8.

title: gingerbread
directions: Beat the first five ingredients together.
Add flour, sifted with salt, cinnamon, ginger, allspice and soda.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Pour mixture into freezer can of electric freezer (or hand-turned).
Freeze according to manufacturer's directions.
Let ripen at least 1 hour (if you can wait!).
Yields 5 quarts.

title: almond fantasy cookies
directions: Work first 6 ingredients together to form a smooth paste.
Add toffee chips.
Roll a spoonful of dough between the palms of hands. Flatten with bottom of glass or cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 325° until golden brown.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Wrap raw oysters with bacon (Sizzlean is better).
Place in pan.
Cook in oven under the broiler.
When done on first side, turn over.
Seasoning comes from bacon.

title: don't stir cherry pie
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk; pour batter over butter.
Don't stir; just leave alone.
Pour fruit over batter; don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cut into bite size pieces and put in bottom of greased casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream and spread over chicken.
Sprinkle crushed crackers over soup.
Pour melted margarine over crackers.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.

title: cheese wafers (snacks)
directions: Process cheese and butter in a food processor until blended.
Add flour, salt and paprika; process until mixture forms a ball, stopping often to scrape down the sides.
Add cereal and almonds; process until blended.
Stop twice to scrape the sides.
Shape dough into 1 inch balls.
Place balls about 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each ball in a crisscross pattern with a fork dipped in flour.
Bake at 350° for 12 -14 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Store in an airtight container.

title: sugared nuts
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
In medium bowl, beat egg white until foamy.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and nuts, coating well.
Spread on a greased baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.

title: good relish
directions: Grind or chop all vegetables together.
Put on salt; stir and set aside for 5 minutes.
Drain off excess water.
Add sugar, vinegar and water.
Put in hot jars and seal.

title: fran's broccoli casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; add flour, salt, milk, cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Cook and stir until sauce boils.
Remove from heat.
Cook broccoli until crisp/tender.
Combine broccoli and cheese sauce; pour into casserole dish.

title: sugarless cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: lo-cal tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl and chill.
Use for sandwiches or with crackers.
Will also stuff 8 tomatoes.

title: grandpa griffin's squirrel and rice
directions: Shoot a squirrel.
Bring home, skin and dress (head and all). Put in pot; season and boil until tender.
Add rice and cook until done.
Serve with hot homemade biscuits and baked sweet taters.

title: too easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crusts from bread slices and cut each slice into 5 fingers.
Place the bread fingers over peaches.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and butter.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: impossible chicken-vegetable pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x
1 1/4-inch.
Mix chicken, zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese.
Spoon evenly into pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients 15 seconds in blender on high speed, 1 minute with wire whisk or hand beater or until smooth.
Pour evenly over chicken mixture.

title: quick chicken enchiladas
directions: Warm shells slightly to prevent cracking.
In each shell, place chicken, a sprinkling of cheese and 1 tablespoon picante sauce.
Roll and place in greased baking dish.
Continue with each roll.
Pour remaining picante sauce and spread cheese evenly over dish.
Bake at 400° until cheese is bubbly, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta with tomato vodka sauce
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet. Add onion; saute until tender (not brown), 5 minutes.
Stir in garlic.
Add tomatoes, vodka and red pepper; break up tomatoes with side of spoon.
Cook until sauce is reduced by 1/3 and thickened, 15 minutes.
Stir in cream; simmer, stirring (do not allow to boil) 5 minutes. Season with salt.

title: baked apple french toast
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish with vegetable oil spray. slice bread into 1-1/2 inch slices. Place bread tightly together in one layer in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or pan.
Place eggs in batter bowl and beat lightly.
Add milk, 1/4 c. sugar and vanilla and mix with 10 inch whisk.
Pour half of liquid over bread.
Peel, core and slice apples.
Cut into rings.
Place apple rings on top of bread to cover.
Pour remaining egg mixture over apples.
Mix remaining 1/2 c. sugar with cinnamon and place in flour/sugar shaker.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 35 minutes.
Cool for 5-10 minutes before serving.
Serve with maple syrup.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruit (reserve juice).
Chop all fruit and cut cherries in halves.
Mix all together in a large mixing bowl. Sprinkle instant pudding mix over fruit.
If fruit seems too thick, add some of the reserved juice. Chill.

title: sugar creme cake
directions: Mix cake mix with butter and 2 eggs.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan (13 x 9-inches).
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and the additional 2 eggs.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour, sugar and salt to make a paste.
Add cheese until it melts.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream to beans.
Top with corn flakes and butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: far east celery
directions: Cook celery in a little boiling water until crisp done, about 8 minutes.
Mix celery with water chestnuts which have been drained and thinly sliced.
Add chicken soup and diced pimento. Place in a one-quart casserole.
Toss breadcrumbs with almonds and melted butter.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until hot.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter; stir in brown sugar and milk. Bring to a boil; boil 2 minutes while stirring.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
Mix in confectioners sugar 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Spread into buttered 9-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Oil pan and sprinkle coconut and pecans over a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.

title: all-bran icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine cereal, sugar, salt, shortening and boiling water.
Stir until shortening is melted. Cool until lukewarm.
Add yeast mixture and stir in eggs. Gradually add flour and mix thoroughly.
Place in large bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.
When ready to use, shape as desired.
Brush with melted butter and let rise in warm place until doubled in size.
Bake at 400` for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen large rolls.

title: blueberry buckle
directions: Mix all ingredients and sprinkle on top of batter.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Measure strawberries into 6-quart pot.
Measure sugar into bowl.
Stir sugar into fruit; mix thoroughly.
Bring mixture to full rolling boil over high heat, stirring constantly, and quickly stir pectin into fruit mixture.
Bring to full rolling boil, stirring constantly, then continue boiling for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Fill jars immediately to 1/8-inch from tops of jars.
Wipe jar rims and threads.
Cover quickly with lids; screw bands tightly.
Check to see if sealed in 4 to 5 minutes.
Makes about 4 (8 ounce) jars.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Saute meat, breaking into small parts as it browns.
Remove casing from sausage as it browns.
Set aside.
Add tomato paste, juice, salt and oregano to meat and simmer 1 hour.
Cook noodles in salted, boiling water until tender.
Prepare a filling by mixing cheese, eggs, oregano, salt and pepper.
Put a layer of sauce in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then alternate with a layer of meat sauce, cheese and noodles. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, corn syrup, butter, vanilla and chocolate. Stir until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust. Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well in large bowl.
Either divide and make 2 small loaves or make 1 large, topping both with tomato catsup.
Cook at 250° for about 2 1/2 hours.
Pack small potatoes and carrots around meat loaf.
Cover with foil and cook the same as meat loaf.

title: banana brunch cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Combine pancake mix, 3/4 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Add banana, milk, egg and oil; mix well.
Spread into prepared pan.
Combine nuts, 1/4 cup brown sugar and margarine; sprinkle evenly over batter. Bake about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and form ball.
Roll in pecans and refrigerate.

title: five-cup salad
directions: In a large decorative bowl, combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: smoked sausage antipasto salad
directions: Brown smoked, sliced sausage in a skillet and drain well on paper towels.
Arrange lettuce on a large serving dish and top with vegetables and sausage.
Add Feta cheese.
Pour dressing over salad and serve.
Total preparation and cooking time:
15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Form into a ball and cover with dried beef.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Combine cabbage, bell peppers and salt; let set for 1 hour, then drain.
Combine with remaining ingredients; mix well and cook for 40 minutes, stirring frequently.
Make a paste of 1/2 cup flour and 1 cup cool water to which is added some of the hot relish mixture to prevent lumping; add this to mixture, stirring rapidly until thick.
Place in hot jars and seal.
Process filled jars in a hot water bath for 10 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 pints.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute green pepper in margarine.
Add spaghetti, Ro-Tel, pepper and onion to cooked chicken.
Stir well until melted.
Add peas and mushrooms.
Place in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, bake at 325° for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Feeds 10 people.
Freezes well.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add and mix eggs (one at a time); add walnuts.
Sift and add next four ingredients, then add bananas.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: magic shell delight
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pudding mix together.
Add milk and mix. Layer crackers in bottom of baking dish (9 x 13); cover with 1/2 of pudding mix.
Make another layer.
Cover with Magic Shell syrup.
Refrigerate several hours or over night.

title: applesauce nut cake
directions: Mix all together and put in a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and egg with a little milk to moisten. Scald milk and add to sugar mixture.
Place in double boiler. Stir constantly until thick. Add vanilla and butter until blended. May add sliced banana for banana pudding.

title: rice krispies peanut butter balls
directions: Combine syrup, sugar and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil.

Reduce heat and add peanut butter, stirring until melted. Pour peanut butter mixture over Rice Krispies in a large bowl. Stir until well mixed and spread into greased 9 x 13 inch pan and press down lightly and cool, cut into bars.

title: state fair funnel cakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, eggs, and milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Heat cooking oil in a deep skillet.
Cover tip of funnel with finger and fill with batter.
Hold funnel over skillet; release batter in circular motion, then crisscross batter to form funnel cake.
Batter will rise and expand while cooking. Cook until golden brown on both sides. Sprinkle with powdered sugar or coat with glaze.
Serve warm.

title: ruth rubendunst's tomato sauce
directions: Scald tomatoes in boiling water.
Peel and seed.
Cut into quarters.
Heat oil in large soup pot over medium heat.
Saute onion, garlic and celery until wilted.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, herbs, salt and pepper, bay leaf and sugar.
Bring to a boil and simmer 2 hours.
Remove bay leaf, cool and pack into freezer containers or 18 ounce jars.
Makes about 6 (18 ounce) containers.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cover raisins with water and cook 5 minutes. Drain.
Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to raisins, along with sour cream, egg yolks (that have been beaten good) and oleo. Cook very slowly, stirring, until mixture thickens.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue and brown.

title: old fashioned tea cakes(1920)
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk, soda, baking powder and flour in small amounts until dough is stiff enough to roll. Roll out or cut in shape desired.
Bake at 300° until lightly colored.

title: grape pie
directions: Slip skins; cook insides and bring to a boil.
Rub out seeds. Add skins and pulp together.
Mix in other ingredients and place in pie shell.
Put crust on top.
Bake in 400° oven until crust is brown, 45 minutes.

title: hearty omelet
directions: Beat all ingredients in a deep bowl with a fork.
Pour into heated, nonstick frypan.
Brown on one side; turn carefully and brown the other side.
Also good for a light meal in the evening.

title: almond fingers
directions: Roll into little fingers.
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes. When cool, roll in confectioners sugar.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add chilies.
Heat through.
Add soup and milk to meat and heat through.
Put thin layer of sauce in bottom of baking dish.
Put each tortilla into sauce and cover with sauce.
When bottom of dish is covered with one layer of tortillas, sprinkle layer of cheese.
Keep layering until sauce and tortillas are used.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix oil and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla and beat well. Sift all dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture. Add oats and nuts and mix well. Dough will be stiff (use hands). Shape into rolls and wrap in waxed paper. Chill in the refrigerator. Slice 1/4-inch thick and bake on ungreased baking sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Yield: about 60 cookies.

title: dinner pockets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease large baking dish.
In skillet, cook sausage, onion and vegetable until sausage browns and vegetables are soft.
Pour off fat; stir in soup.
Divide dough into 6 equal parts.
On floured surface, roll out 1 part to a 6 inch round.
Spread mixture in skillet on 1/2 of round.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Fold over and pinch sides together.
Place on baking dish.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with sesame seeds.
Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: how to cook a christmas turkey
directions: Put black syrup on it.
Just a little salt, just a little pepper.
Put soup on top of it.
Stuff with ice cream.
Cook 5 minutes at 1°.
Serve with macaroni.

title: molasses cake(very old family recipe)
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add egg, then molasses.
Mix together flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Last, add water.
Bake in 8-inch square pan approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 2 to 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble 1/3 of the cake into the bottom of a large bowl.
Add a layer of pudding, then cherries, pineapple, Cool Whip and then top off with pecan pieces.
Repeat the process again ending with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: catfish soup
directions: Place all ingredients into stew pan and put on slow fire. Stir occasionally and cook until fish is ready to fall to pieces. Serve hot.

title: cranberry surprise loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour BOTTOM ONLY of a 9 x 5 loaf pan.
In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg and blend well.
Set aside.
Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.
In large bowl, mix together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Stir in apple juice, margarine and beaten eggs.
Fold in cranberries and nuts.
Spoon half of batter into prepared pan.
Spoon cream cheese mixture evenly over batter.
Top with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: orange sherbet mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water and allow to jell slightly.
Mix in sherbet thoroughly.
Add drained pineapple and oranges.
Mix well. Refrigerate until firm.

title: blueberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Mix the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend in shortening. Stir in egg.
Add enough boiling water to orange juice and rind to measure 1 cup.
Stir into flour mixture.
Add blueberries and nuts; stir gently.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 60 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13 x 6-inch ovenproof dish.
Heat water and sugar until sugar melts.
Cut shortening into flour until particles are like fine crumbs.
Add milk and stir only until dough leaves side of bowl.
Turn out on floured board into ball or rectangle about 1/4-inch thick.
Roll like jelly roll, slice into 16 slices, 1/2-inch thick.
Place fruit on bottom of prepared dish, then put dough slices over fruit.
Pour sugar syrup over rolls.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven-fried potatoes
directions: Halve potatoes lengthwise and slice into 1/2-inch thick strips.
Put margarine and olive oil in bowl.
Add potatoes, tossing to coat well.
Arrange potato strips in single layer on nonstick baking sheet.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Combine ingredients in a shallow bowl or bag.
Melt butter and shortening in pan.
Place chicken skin side down.
Cook, uncovered, 30 minutes.
Turn chicken; cook, uncovered, 30 minutes more.

title: italian garlic dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; blend.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: fresh coconut cake
directions: Lightly grease three 9-inch layer pans.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cream the butter and sugar and add 1 egg at a time.
Add flour which has been sifted once, then measured, alternately with milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth. Add vanilla and a handful of coconut.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: ginger and peach chicken
directions: Spray a large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Over medium heat, cook chicken in skillet 8 to 10 minutes until browned and no longer pink, turning.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat and mix well the egg yolks, lemon juice, rind and butter; set aside. Mix sugar, flour and salt. Measure milk. Whip egg whites. Add sugar mixture alternately with the milk. Fold into beaten egg whites. Pour into 8-inch square pan. Place this pan in a pan of water. Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven. Pudding will be in the bottom of pan. Turn over when served and
top with Cool Whip.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Beat egg and milk together.
Stir in melted butter.
Mix all together.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: applesauce cake no. 1
directions: Bake in slow oven for 3/4 hour.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix flour, baking powder, and sugar together using a fork.
Cut in shortening until it has the consistency of cornmeal.
Add cheese.
Stir in buttermilk all at one time until just blended.
Do not overmix.
Drop by tablespoonfuls (or use an ice cream scoop) onto a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bake pie crust and let cool.
Place chopped strawberries in pie crust.
Combine all other ingredients in boiler and bring to a boil.
Pour into pie crust.
Place in refrigerator.
Add Cool Whip or whipping cream when ready to serve.

title: shrimp or crawfish delight
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add soups, tomatoes, seasoned shrimp or crawfish and parsley.
Bring to a boil, then add raw rice.
Mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven, covered, for 1 hour. Stir (with a fork) after first 30 minutes.
Finish baking.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel potatoes.
Boil and mash with butter and cream cheese. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and refrigerate mixture overnight.
Bake the next day in 350° oven for 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: apple cake pie
directions: Peel and slice apples into greased 10-inch pie pan.
Cover with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream butter, 1/2 cup sugar and beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients; mix.
Spread over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: In Dutch oven, cook ground beef, onion and garlic until beef is browned and onion tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove meat sauce from heat and stir in drained spaghetti.	Place half in a 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with rest of spaghetti mix.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until heated.

title: kahlua cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients by hand.
Don't use mixer.
Will be very thick.
Add chocolate chips.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake 60 minutes in 350° oven. Cool upright at least 25 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, oleo and milk.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter, oatmeal and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 350° (175°C) if you use shiny metal cookie sheet.
Or, heat to 325° (165°C) for dark metal sheet. Cream together thoroughly the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Beat chocolate.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Measure milk; blend in dry ingredients with milk.
Add nuts.
Chill 3 hours.
Form 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet, 2 or 3 inches apart.
Place cookies in center of oven.
Bake for about 15 minutes.
Cool cookies slightly.
Remove from the cookie sheet with turner; place on racks or paper toweling to cool.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine eggs, brown sugar, milk, pumpkin, salt and spices. Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Beat egg whites; add sugar and beat until stiff.
Soak gelatine in cold water.
Stir into double boiler.
Chill until pumpkin mixture is partly set.
Fold in egg white mixture.
Pour in pie shell and chill until set.
Garnish with whip cream.

title: mexican fudge
directions: Grate cheeses together.
Mix eggs and picante sauce together. Put 1/2 of cheeses in bottom of Pyrex dish (oblong).
Put the egg and picante mixture on top of cheese.
Cover with the remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut in squares and place each piece on Doritos or tortilla chips.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds and chill overnight. Sprinkle toasted almonds on top of chicken salad just before serving.
If you like, serve on lettuce garnished with wedges of your favorite melon.
Yields 12 servings.

title: tater tots casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, salt and pepper in a skillet. Drain.
Pour meat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix together and put in loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cider punch
directions: Makes 2 gallons.
It is good hot.
I omit the ginger ale.

title: date surprise balls
directions: Beat eggs with a spoon in a 2-quart pan.
Add sugar, butter and dates. Cook slowly for 10 to 12 minutes on a low fire.
Remove from heat and cool. Add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Shape into small balls. Roll in shredded coconut.

title: emily lee ann's poppy seed bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pan or 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Mix all ingredients and beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake until wooden pick comes out clean; 9-inch loaf for 55 to 65 minutes or 8 1/2-inch loaves for 55 to 60 minutes.
Take out of oven and cool for 2 to 3 minutes, then take out of pan.
Leave to cool (upright) on wire rack.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix pecans and coconut.
Put in bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to box directions. Pour over pecans and coconut.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, butter and vanilla.
Spoon over cake mix. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Mix with other ingredients.
Let rise until double in size.
Push down.
Let rise again.
Push down.
Make into rolls and put into pan.
Let rise.
Bake in 400° oven until done.
Handle dough easy and lightly or rolls will be tough.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni and tomatoes according to directions on the box.
Mix in hamburger.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: favorite family recipe - christmas stollen
directions: Soften active dry yeast in warm water.
Scald milk in sugar, salt and butter; cool to lukewarm.
Mix in 2 cups flour, yeast, eggs, cardamom and fruit.
Add enough remaining flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead on floured surface; place in a greased bowl and grease top of dough.
Cover.

title: rum balls
directions: Cream all ingredients, but only half the nuts.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls and then roll balls into remaining nuts to coat.
Keep chilled.

title: melt-a-way
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix ingredients and roll or drop small amount on a greased cookie sheet.
Cook 6 to 8 minutes (until set and not brown).
Remove from cookie sheet and roll in confectioners sugar.

title: peach cheesecake ice cream
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine softened cream cheese and sugar.
Beat with an electric mixer on medium-high speed until fluffy.
Reduce mixer speed to low and gradually add whipping cream, milk, peach nectar or orange juice, lemon juice, vanilla and apple pie spice.
Beat until ingredients are combined.
Stir in the chopped peach.
Freeze the ice cream mixture in a 1 or 2-quart ice cream freezer, according to manufacturer's directions. Makes about 1 quart.

title: orange danish rolls
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and peel; mix until well blended. Unroll dough from cans and lay on floured surface.
Overlap long edges to shape into a rectangle (13 x 7-inch), pressing all edges together to seal.
Spread rectangle with cream cheese mixture (3/4 of mixture, save 1/4 for icing).
Roll up dough, starting at long side, roll up (jelly roll fashion).
Cut or slice 1-inch pieces. Lay on cookie sheet on cut side about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cool summer lemon roll
directions: In bowl, blend together cake mix and lemon pie filling.
On a parchment paper lined cookie sheet, spread batter evenly to within 1-inch of edge of cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 13 to 16 minutes or until lightly browned.
Carefully take cake out of pan by lifting up ends of parchment paper at the same time.
Leave on counter for exactly 8 minutes.
Then roll up cake into a roll and cover ends with paper towels or plastic wrap.
Let it cool completely before unrolling, approximately 2 hours.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream butter and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Blend in pretzels. Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool. Cream together cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Fold into Cool Whip. Pour into cooled crust.
Dissolve jello in boiling water and add undrained strawberries.
When jello mixture is partially set, pour it over the cream mixture in shell.
Chill.
Serves 12.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut up chicken.
Add and mix all other ingredients together.

title: holiday cranberry freeze
directions: Mix ingredients and put in freezer.
Serve semi-frozen.
Great for Christmas or Thanksgiving dinner.

title: brown sugar chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into an unbaked pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until center of pie is firm when shaken.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and stir ground beef; drain off all fat.
Add spaghetti sauce to meat and mix well.
Heat oven to 350°.
Mix Ricotta cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, parsley flakes and oregano.
In an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer 1/4 each of noodles, meat sauce, Mozzarella cheese and the cottage cheese mixture.
Repeat 3 times.
Add meat sauce over top and sprinkle (cover well) with Parmesan cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Rinse with cold water and drain well. Add chopped celery and onion. Combine oil, vinegar, mayonnaise, salt and cayenne pepper.
Mix well.
Pour over peas.
Stir gently. Allow to chill in refrigerator several hours or overnight.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute pepper in butter until tender.
Blend in flour.
Add milk and stock.
Cook until smooth.
Add cheese, pimento and soup. Cook spaghetti in broth and drain.
Add sauce and chicken.
Pour into casserole.
Sprinkle with additional cheese.
Bake at 250° to 300° for 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry delight dump cake
directions: Dump cherry filling in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan.
Then dump pineapple.
Then sprinkle cake mix on top of that.
Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
On top of this add Angel Flake coconut and top with pecans.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve warm with ice cream or it's good cold.
Serve from the same pan.

title: bacon greens
directions: Cook bacon completely, but not crispy.
Cook greens for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir thoroughly. Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: flan(spanish caramel custard)
directions: Pour milk into a large saucepan.
Add salt and scald.
Remove from fire and add 1 cup of sugar, stirring until it is dissolved; set aside.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together powdered sugar, evaporated milk and peanut butter.
Mix in cream cheese, half of dry peanuts and Dream Whip. Once all mixed, pour into pie shell of your choice.
Sprinkle remaining dry peanuts on top.
Freeze for 2 hours, then refrigerate until ready for use.
Serve with chocolate syrup and Cool Whip.

title: colorful slaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease (Crisco) a 9x13 baking dish.
Peel and slice potatoes. Make a layer of potato slices, top with velveeta cheese and 4 tsp butter on cheese.
Repeat layers.
Mix milk and flour together. Pour over layers.
Cover and Bake at 350 - 400 degrees for 1 1/2 hours or until potatoes are tender.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook beef with onions.
Prepare tortilla and assemble one at a time.
Fry tortilla in hot oil for a few seconds on each side. Dip into 1 can of heated enchilada sauce and remove immediately. Place on a plate and put olives, cheese and meat mixture on tortilla.
Roll up and place seam side down in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
When all enchiladas are in baking dish, cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese, olives and raw chopped onions.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: diabetic pineapple cookies
directions: Sift the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg, margarine and rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle coconut on each cookie and level with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: juanita cole farlowe's pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat eggs slightly with fork.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla. Add cold milk.
Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into custard cups.
Sprinkle with nutmeg, if desired, and place in 2 or 2 1/2-inch deep pan.
Pour boiling water around cups to come almost level with custard.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until a silver knife comes out clean when inserted in center. Makes 6 average sized custards.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper; add to other ingredients. Set in refrigerator overnight, then drain and serve.

title: nut brittle
directions: Melt sugar over low flame until sugar is golden brown.
Add butter.
Add nuts and stir until nuts are covered.
Pour into well buttered dish.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: cherry mash candy
directions: Mix
ingredients
together
well.
Chill
and form into balls or	any
shape
you
prefer.
Chill another 30 minutes. Melt
over simmering	water 1 pound dark chocolate (sometimes called almond bark).
Dip chilled balls into melted chocolate, after
stirring in	8 ounces finely chopped, unsalted peanuts into melted chocolate.

title: cheese cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; chill until it starts to jell.
Mix together cream cheese and confectioners sugar until smooth.
Whip Milnot until it peaks; slowly add cream cheese mixture and gelatin.
Mix cracker crumbs with margarine, reserving 1/4 cup.
Line a cake pan with rest of crumbs.
Pour in cream cheese mixture.
Sprinkle with rest of crumbs.
Chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crumble Oreos; set aside.
Fold together the remaining ingredients.
Layer as follows: pudding, Oreos, pudding, Oreos, etc., for a total of 4 or 5 layers.
End with one inch of Oreos on top.
(These may be ground fine in a blender so as to resemble dirt.)
Optional: Add gummy worms to layers.

title: frosting for "lazy daisy" cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread on a baked Lazy Daisy Cake.
Place under the heated broiler in oven until it bubbles. Delicious!

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix jello with 1 cup boiling water and set aside to cool. Beat Milnot until stiff and set aside.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Add cooled jello to whipped Milnot, then cheese mixture and vanilla.

title: banana muffins
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Mix dry with moist ingredients, stirring until all are moist.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in melted margarine.
Remove chicken from pan. Drain pineapple, reserving juice. Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in skillet.
Gradually add vinegar, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Stir. Cook over medium heat until thick.
You may need to add about 1/2 cup water. Add pineapple, green pepper, onion and chicken.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Saute onion and shrimp in butter until tender.
Add broccoli; simmer 5 minutes.
Add cheese soup and rice.
Put mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili chill chasen(microwave)
directions: Combine onion, green pepper and crumbled ground beef in a plastic container and microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Drain and place in a 2-quart container.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, beans, salt, pepper, chili powder and dry mustard.
Cover and microwave on High for 10 to 12 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking. Standing time is 10 minutes.
Cooking time is 16 to 18 minutes. Serves 4 to 8.

title: oven fried parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Dip chicken in salad dressing; dredge in bread crumb mixture.
Place chicken bone side down in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion and garlic in margarine over medium heat until soft.
Add meat and brown.
Add flour, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Cook 5 minutes.
Add soup and simmer uncovered for 10 minutes. Stir in sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Sprinkle with parsley. Serve with noodles.

title: dirt cake
directions: In blender or food processor, add 8 to 10 cookies at a time and blend until finely crushed.
Set aside.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix pudding according to package directions.
In a 2-quart casserole dish, layer half the Trefoils, half the bananas, half the pudding and half the whipped topping.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate 4 hours.
Before serving, top with crushed Juliettes.

title: my hawaiian pudding
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly, about 3 to 4 minutes.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, banana and egg until well blended.
Stir in chocolate or butterscotch bits.
Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: april fools apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, water, cream of tartar and butter.
Bring to a boil, add cinnamon and continue to boil for approximately 4 minutes stirring constantly.
Crush the saltine crackers and put in a 9 inch unbaked pie crust.
Pour mixture from saucepan into crust and sprinkle extra cinnamon over top.
Bake for 40 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water until dissolved. Add frozen berries. Cool until slightly thickened. Tear cake into pieces. Put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix Cool Whip and strawberry mixture. Fold in slightly. Pour over cake. Refrigerate until set. Yield: 12 to 15 servings.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Measure all ingredients except flour into a small bowl.
Beat until mixture is soft and well blended.
Add flour and mix to a stiff dough.
Measure by level tablespoonful.
Roll each measure of dough into a small ball, placed on ungreased cookie sheets.
Press down lightly with fork.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes or just until very lightly browned.
Remove from oven and serve warm. Also very good reheated.

title: fresh peach pie(variations for strawberry and blueberry)
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Remove from stove and add peach jello.
Cool.
Add peaches and stir until coated and thickened.
Put into prebaked pie shell.
Add Cool Whip or topping.

title: butter cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 11-inch oblong pan with margarine.
Mix first three ingredients by hand.
Press into bottom of pan.

title: mandarin salad
directions: Cook the almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted and almonds are coated.
Cool and break apart.
Store at room temperature.

title: pumpkin pie anytime of the year
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and blend on medium for 1 minute.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Pour into buttered pie pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Let cool and serve with low fat whipped cream.

title: pinto beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Add all ingredients and cook very slow until tender in enough water to cover the beans.
Add any other spices to suit your taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Save broth.
Melt butter.
Mix with stuffing and seasonings.
Mix both soups with broth.
Cook mixed vegetables in separate container with grated cheese.
In greased casserole, layer dressing mix, chicken and soup.
Repeat, ending with dressing mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: fluff cakes(pan cakes)
directions: Mix in order and fry on a griddle.

title: sausage brunch casserole
directions: Place 6 slices buttered bread, buttered side up, in large baking pan.
Place 1/2 sausage that has been cooked and drained and 1/2 cheese over bread.
Beat eggs and milk together.
Pour 1/2 of this over sausage mixture.
Place other 6 slices of bread on top, rest of sausage, cheese, milk and eggs.
Push down with hands.
Make the day before and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top should be crusty brown.

title: creamy freezer pie
directions: Pour milk into ice trays and freeze until almost frozen at edges.
Put ice cold milk into cold bowl and mix with cold beaters at high speed until fluffy.
Add sugar and your favorite flavor Kool-Aid; whip until stiff.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan that has been lined with vanilla wafers; piling high.
Freeze until firm 3 to 4 hours.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Salt and pepper tomato slices.
Dip tomato slices into beaten eggs, then into flour.
Drop into deep hot oil; let fry until golden brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Serve alone or with meal.

title: ice cream and rice chex dessert
directions: Brown 1 package slivered almonds in 2 tablespoons margarine. Melt 1/4 cup butter/margarine; add remaining ingredients. Put 1/2 mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add 2 quarts ice cream.
Cover with other half of Chex mixture.
Freeze.

title: potato, ham and cheese casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine ham, potatoes, margarine, salt, pepper and milk, in a large saucepan, with just enough water to cover ham and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Add flour and water to thicken.
Add 1 cup of cheese and pimiento; stir until well-mixed.

title: taco casserole
directions: Cook hamburger according to taco seasoning directions.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer the crushed chips, meat, refried beans, sour cream, cheese and finally sprinkle on the tomatoes and/or olives. Put in 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: russian tea
directions: Bring to a boil and continue to boil for 5 minutes the water, sugar, cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Add tea bags and brew for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add orange juice, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Better next day after refrigerated.

title: mama's coffee cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; then add the milk and egg.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: pumpkin crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Spray bottom of 9 X 13 pan. Combine pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl. Pour into pan. Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over pumpkin mixture, top with pecans. Drizzle with melted butter over pecans. Bake 50-55 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool and serve chilled. Top with cool whip when serving.

title: wanda's vegetable soup
directions: Cook and dice meat.
Save broth.
Saute onions, celery, green peppers and garlic in olive or vegetable oil; add remaining ingredients.
Add choice of rice, pasta or potato.
Add salt and pepper.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix these ingredients.
Line 1 1/2-quart casserole with Pepperidge Farm seasoned bread crumbs.
Pour in squash mixture. Top with more bread crumbs and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: aggression cookies(make with children)
directions: Mix with hands until smooth.
Shape into balls; flatten on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt
1 stick (or less) margarine in iron skillet.
Add 1
cup rice
and	brown
lightly,
stirring
constantly.	Put browned rice
in casserole; add 1 can undiluted beef consomme and
1 can undiluted onion soup.
Place in preheated 325° oven and
cook
for 1	hour
and
15 minutes in covered casserole. Delicious!!

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble half of cake and layer half of the ingredients in order listed.
Continue layering, beginning with last half of cake and ending with Cool Whip.
Garnish with nuts, coconut, cherries, etc.
Be sure to use punch bowl.
It makes a large quantity.

title: taco soup
directions: Add all ingredients together.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
You can add hot sauce, if desired.
This can be frozen.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix water with jello; then add pie filling and pineapple.
Let jell in fridge.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla and spread over top of jello mix.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped pecans on top.
Store in refrigerator.

title: simple meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order in which they are listed. Stir thoroughly.
Press into a greased loaf tin and bake in a 350° preheated oven for one hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add sour cream and topping.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Chill.

title: cherries emily
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and margarine; press into 1 1/2-quart oblong Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cream the cheese and milk.
Gradually add sugar.
Spread mix over graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle pecans over cream cheese mixture.
Whip cream with vanilla.
Spread over pecans.
Chill.
When cold, spread cherry pie filling on top.
Chill overnight.

title: one-pot pork chop supper
directions: In skillet, brown chops.
Pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover; cook over low heat 45 minutes or until tender. Yields 4 servings.

title: alligator fingers
directions: Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to flour and cornmeal.
Coat gator strips with the mixture.
Deep fry in vegetable oil.

title: san francisco oyster loaf ala chase
directions: Cut lid off bread.
Hollow out loaf.
Clean the oysters and dredge in flour or cracker meal.
Place oysters in frying pan with the olive oil and simmer on both sides until done, approximately 6 minutes. Butter inside of loaf.
Place oysters in loaf.
Replace lid and bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes.
Add and season with remaining ingredients to taste, especially the lemon which brings flavor to its peak. Serves 4 to 6.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Begin by melting 3 tablespoons of butter in pan; allow to melt and become hot.
Roll chicken strips in flour and place in pan. Cook chicken halfway and then add spices, onions and peppers. When chicken is almost done, add stock, rest of the vegetables and poppy seed dressing.
Toss all ingredients in pan and serve over a bed of rice.
Only toss for 30 to 40 seconds.

title: carol's strawberry pie
directions: Mix together syrup, sugar, cornstarch, salt and add water slowly and cook until clear.
Add Jell-O; stir until dissolved. Cool and add berries.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill, then add Cool Whip on top.

title: strawberry cream puffs
directions: Melt butter with boiling water in a small saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt; cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture leaves sides of pan in a smooth ball.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Drop mixture by heaping spoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Cool. Cut top off cream puffs and fill with sweetened strawberries.
Top with whipped cream.
Replace tops and garnish with whipped cream and whole strawberries.
Yields 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer apples in the bottom 8 by 8 inch square of baking dish.
Combine water, cinnamon and salt, sprinkle mixture over apples.
Work together the sugar, flour and butter until crumbly. Spread crumb mixture over apples.
Bake uncovered about 40 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Mix coconut, sour cream and the entire bag of marshmallows, torn into halves.
Drain pineapple chunks, reserving juice.
Add pineapple.
Drain mandarin oranges and discard juice.
Add oranges to mixture, reserving about 1 dozen to garnish.
Blend together gently.
Add some juice and mix again.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet potato puff
directions: Combine potatoes, margarine and seasonings; mix well.
Place in 1-quart casserole.
Top with Marshmallow Creme.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: butter nut chewies
directions: Mix together and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs and vanilla and mix thoroughly.
Add dry ingredients and water, then stir in oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: vegetable tray
directions: On a large round serving plate, place lettuce in the center. Around the lettuce, place the onions, sliced tomatoes, radishes, cucumbers, celery and carrots. Serve with a Curry Dip.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pineapple with juice and soda; mix well.
In large bowl, combine cake mix and remaining ingredients.
Add pineapple mixture.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Do not under bake.
Cool in pan
for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan, finish cooling on rack.

title: eggplant bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix crumbs, oregano and garlic.
Dip eggplant slices in butter, then in crumb mixture.
Place in single layer on sprayed jelly roll pan.
Spread evenly with sauce. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes with skins on; salt lightly.
Put cold water on them to hasten cooling to handle.
Peel and cut into cubes.
Mince bacon; fry until crisp.
Combine onion, vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and mustard; heat.
Add potatoes, bacon and parsley. Heat slowly and mix to flavor potatoes.

title: oriental pork and noodles
directions: Bring large pot of water to a boil.
Add pasta; cook until tender.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
While pasta cooks, spray a large nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Heat over medium-high heat.
Add pork.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir often. Remove from skillet.
Spray skillet again.
Add bell pepper and carrots.
Stir over medium-high heat 2 to 3 minutes until veggies are crisp and tender.
Stir in corn and scallions.
Mix remaining ingredients until well blended.
Stir into skillet.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 30 seconds or until thickened and clear.
Stir in pasta and pork.
Cook until heated through.

title: haystacks
directions: *White chocolate or dark chocolate may be substituted for butterscotch.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple (not drained) to boil.
Add jello; stir well. Let mixture cool.
Add buttermilk.
Let cool.
Let Cool Whip soften.
Stir in last.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.

title: patti's icing
directions: Mix together at high speed for 5 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium size bowl, with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning mix in another bowl.

title: raisin sauce for ham
directions: Mix cornstarch in cold water.
Add remaining ingredients. Cook on medium heat to desired thickness.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper, paprika, thyme and onion.
Set aside. Melt margarine in a shallow baking pan in a 400 degree oven. Remove baking pan from oven.
Dip chicken pieces in buttermilk, then in flour mixture.
Place in buttered pan and turn to coat with butter.
Bake in 400 degree oven for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken. Bake another 30 minutes or until tender.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Break up Ramen noodles (do not use seasoning packet). Saut in margarine with sunflower seeds until noodles are light brown. Add almonds; mix.

title: rum pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Soak gelatin in water, put over flame until boiling.
Add nutmeg.
Pour over sugar and eggs slowly.
Mix well.
Beat cream until stiff and add rum.
Fold in egg yolk mixture.
Pour into shell and chill.
Sprinkle with shaved chocolate.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and butter together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix with beater the cream cheese, powdered sugar, 2 eggs and pecans.
Spread on cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Layer coconut; layer pecans.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Spread over pecans.
Mix together margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Glob over cake by teaspoonfuls.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cake will be shakey but will set up when cool.

title: carrot-raisin salad
directions: Shred carrots to make 4 cups.
Stir in raisins and salt.
If your raisins are too hard, steam them for 1 minute in the microwave.

title: dawn's focaccia bread
directions: Spread even coat of olive oil on each piece of bread. Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine all above ingredients in a bowl and mix.
Spread a generous amount of topping on each piece of bread and bake in oven for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: In large pot, combine everything, except catsup.
Boil until water is gone.
Drain and discard grease.
Add catsup and simmer about 30 minutes.
Makes approximately 1 gallon.

title: sauerkraut with spareribs
directions: Put ribs in pan, season and bake at 450° for 20 minutes. Take ribs out of pan and put sauerkraut and remaining ingredients in.
Place ribs on top of sauerkraut and bake at 350° for 1 1/2
to 2 hours.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt margarine in dish in oven.
Add rice and onion and bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Add consomme and stir.
Add mushrooms and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocaroons
directions: Start the oven at 300°. Add salt to egg whites. Beat until eggs are frothy. Beat in sugar, about 2 tablespoons at a time. Add vanilla. Gently stir in coconut, corn flakes and chocolate. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes. Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: california curried couscous(serves 6)
directions: Bring chicken broth with curry to boil in medium saucepan. Stir in couscous; cover and reduce to low heat.
Cook 5 minutes. Remove from heat and fluff with a fork.
Cover until needed. While couscous cooks, saute garlic, celery and onion in olive oil over medium heat until soft, but not browned, about 5 minutes. Combine chutney and lemon juice in small bowl.
Toss couscous with onion/celery mixture.
Stir pine nuts, currants and green onions into chutney mixture in small frying pan over low heat.
Pour over couscous and stir to combine.

title: quick macaroni and cheese
directions: Place macaroni in microwave bowl, layering with butter and cheese.
Pour milk over mixture.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes, stirring several times.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: goblin bread
directions: Mix well and spread into cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini; drain and add spinach, cheese and ham.
Toss with dressing.

title: vegetables dip
directions: Mix together the Hidden Valley Ranch dressing and onion soup mix with sour cream.
Let stand overnight before using.
Makes a good dip for vegetables.

title: unbaked new year's cookies
directions: Melt chips over hot water and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let dry and store in airtight container.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Make cake according to package directions. When cool, spread crushed pineapple on top of cake.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Cook chicken until tender in a large pot of boiling water. Remove chicken, saving broth!
Remove meat from bone.
Mix all the dressing ingredients well (it will be real soupy).
Pour half of the mixture into a greased oblong baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on top and cover with remaining dressing mixture.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: mammy's chicken and dumplings
directions: Wash chicken very good.
Put whole chicken in large roaster with water covering chicken.
Put 1/2 stick butter on top of chicken and cook until tender.
Remove chicken to pan to be browned under broiler before serving.

title: stuffed oranges
directions: Mash potatoes, vanilla extract, sugar, margarine, eggs and orange extract together; set aside.
Cut oranges in half and remove pulp (do not use veins).
Mix into potato mixture and place in orange shell.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove and put marshmallows on top, place 1 cherry on top and return to oven at 350° until top is melted and lightly brown.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, potato chips and almonds.
Place in a large rectangle dish.
Top with cheese, chips and almonds. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen rocky road
directions: Mix all
together, then fold in 1 cup of whipped cream. Freeze in Pyrex pan.
Let thaw just enough to cut in squares.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Grate cheese. Add Miracle Whip, milk and pimentos. Mix thoroughly. Use for sandwiches or as a dip.

title: potato casserole
directions: Slice potatoes thin.
Line bottom of dish.
Slice onion over potatoes.
Shake Krazy salt over.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over this.
Keep adding layers to make amount you want.
Add milk to dish.
Dot generously with butter.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.
May add peppers.
Makes it pretty as well as adds flavor.

title: mary jane's squash
directions: Slice squash crosswise into wheels.
Layer in saucepan with sliced onion, salt, pepper and butter (dotted on squash).
Put pan on medium heat and when lid is hot, turn down to simmer and stir from time to time until tender, about 1/2 hour altogether.

title: cherry pie with crumble top
directions: Pour pie filling into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all other ingredients together until well mixed.
Sprinkle over top of pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: garlic cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili powder and paprika.
Shape and roll into this.

title: cream cheese rhubarb pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 2-quart saucepan, combine the rhubarb, cornstarch, salt and 1 cup of the sugar.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until the mixture boils and thickens.
Pour the rhubarb mixture into the unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and set aside.
Reduce the oven temperature to 350°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate to blend flavors about 1 hour. Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate oat dream candy
directions: Stir until cool
and
drop
on
waxed paper or put into lightly buttered dish until fully cooked.

title: tea cakes
directions: Put butter and margarine on stove and let it melt.
Put flour in bread tray and sprinkle cinnamon over it.
Mix eggs and sugar in a bowl and stir and beat until smooth.
Then pour this into the flour.
Add melted butter and margarine.
Mix good until real stiff.
Roll out dough real thin and use a saucer to cut out the tea cakes.
Sprinkle sugar on top and cook.

title: watergate salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Add pudding mix, pineapple and nuts.
Mix and store in refrigerator.
May be topped with cherries.

title: sangria
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large pitcher, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Add club soda just before serving.
Serve over ice.
Makes about 1 quart.

title: beefsteak pizzaiola
directions: While flank steak is partially frozen, slice into 1/4 x 2-inch strips. Allow to completely thaw.
Heat oil in a large skillet until almost smoking.
Sear steak on both sides.
Add onion, garlic, tomatoes, bell pepper and herbs.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour, adding water if liquid boils off. Add mushrooms and wine. Continue to simmer until mushrooms are cooked. Serve with white rice.
Serves 6 people.

title: apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place in layers in greased 9 or 10-inch square baking dish apples, sugar and dry cake mix.
Pour melted margarine over top of cake mix.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: cloud biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut into shortening.
Combine egg and milk with a fork.
Add to first mixture.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 to 14 minutes.
Very light and delicious.

title: leftover meat pie
directions: Heat gravy.
Add cubed meat, cubed or mashed potatoes and peas.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes and then for about 20 additional minutes at 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Let Cool Whip stand at room temperature.
Drain juice from fruit; mix pudding.
Put some of each on each layer of cake.
Save a few for top layer.
This will fill a large punch bowl and costs about $15.00.
Make cake and let cool.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine cake mix, fruit cocktail with syrup, 1 cup coconut and the eggs in large mixing bowl.
Blend, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan and sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: two-corn casserole
directions: Saute first three ingredients.
Place in 2 qt. casserole dish. Add next 3 ingredients.
Blend until mixed.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 45-55 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: romanian cabbage soup with bacon(ciorba teraneasca)
directions: You will
need a large soup pot.
Chop up one slice of bacon, and fry it in a heavy stewpan until the fat runs.
Fry the onions in the fat until they are golden.
Add the peppers and fry them, too.
Remove the stewpan from the heat.
Layer the cabbage and the rest of the bacon into the soup pot.
Season between the layers with salt, pepper and the herbs.
Pour the water over it all and bring to a boil.

title: grilled french bread
directions: Mix butter, parsley, onions, garlic powder and celery salt. Cut bread into 1-inch slices, cutting to bottom crust but not through.
Spread butter mixture on each slice.
Wrap in heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Heat over hot coals for about 20 minutes.
Turn often during heating.

title: french vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until bubbles appear around edge of mixture in pan.
Cool to room temperature.
Stir in vanilla and cream.
Pour into freezer can and freeze.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: rise 'n shine shake
directions: Reserve 3 strawberries.
In blender, put in remaining strawberries, banana, milk, yogurt and honey.
Cover; blend at medium-low until thick and smooth.
Pour into chilled glasses; sprinkle with nutmeg.
Garnish with strawberry.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Soften butter.
Add remaining ingredients except confectioners sugar and mix together well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar on top of brownies while they are still hot.

title: banana bread
directions: *Can use buttermilk or 2 tablespoons milk and 1 tablespoon vinegar, combined.

title: red snapper court-bouillon(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Pour tomatoes in a large roasting pan over stove.
Cut garlic into tiny pieces and add to pan.
Add mushrooms.
Salt and pepper a whole dressed snapper.
Place in roasting pan.
Pour sauce over fish and bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Baste every 15 minutes with sauce.
Remove fish and thicken sauce with flour.
Add Worcestershire.
Serve over hot rice.

title: nachos
directions: Spread out the nachos in a single layer on a baking sheet. Cook the onion with the meat until no pink remains, but do not brown.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning; combine well.
Place a spoonful of meat mixture on each chip and sprinkle grated cheese over all.
Place under preheated broiler for 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese has melted.
Sprinkle tomato and lettuce over all. Serve at once.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix ingredients and press into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: applesauce
directions: Put in
a crock-pot (slow cooker) and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: cole slaw for freezing
directions: Shred these ingredients medium fine.
Mix all together and let stand 1 hour.
Make syrup for cole slaw and let cool.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except nuts; stir just until moistened.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes.
Check with toothpick.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a large nonstick Dutch oven, heat the oil on medium heat. Add chicken. Cook until lightly browned, turning once, about 8 minutes.

Transfer to a plate and keep warm. Add bell pepper, onion and jalapeo pepper to pan. Cook for 5 minutes. Stir in rice. Saut for 1 minute. Add the broth, water and tomatoes with liquid. Break up tomatoes with a spoon. Return chicken to pan.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Serve hot. (Hamburger or sausage may be added.)

title: cranberry-apple waldorf
directions: In large bowl, mix unflavored gelatine with sugar.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved, about 5 minutes.
Stir in cranberry juice.
Chill, stirring occasionally, until mixture is consistency of unbeaten egg whites, about 45 minutes.
Fold in remaining ingredients.

title: delicious vegetable dip
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Then serve with fresh vegetables.
Mixture is best made day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: nany's pound cake
directions: Start with cold oven.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly after each addition.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream oil, sugar, milk, vanilla and egg.
Slowly add and stir in flour, salt and soda.
Stir in M&M's, but do not overstir.
Add cookie dough to baking sheet (1 tablespoon for larger cookies) and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: skillet meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, soup mix and sour cream.
Add bread crumbs or oatmeal if too runny.
Form into loaf.
Place in skillet and cover with tomato soup.
Cover and cook on medium heat for 50 minutes or until done.

title: lazy day cobbler
directions: Put margarine in deep dish and melt in oven or microwave.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Beat to a smooth batter.
Pour over melted butter.
Do not stir.
Empty cherries (not drained) over batter.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Butter will rise to top.

title: light and lively salad
directions: Mix together pudding and pie filling and pineapple.
Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Chill in mold in refrigerator. Unmold and sprinkle with nuts.
(Cherries may be added, if desired.)

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Put chicken in bottom of baking dish. Cut up boiled eggs on top of chicken. Mix can of cream of chicken and can of chicken broth. Pour over chicken. Mix flour with partly melted butter. Mix in milk and pour over chicken. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, until golden brown.

title: funnel cakes
directions: In mixing bowl combine eggs and milk. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt. Add to egg mixture. Beat until smooth. In deep skillet heat oil to 360 degrees. Cover funnel spout with finger. Pour 1/4 cup batter into funnel. Remove finger and release batter into oil in a spiral, starting in the center and working out. Fry from 2-3 minutes until golden brown. Turn carefully. Cool 1 minute. Drain on paper towel and dust with powdered sugar.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Dissolve cherry gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in the lemonade concentrate.
Add cold water and cranberry juice cocktail.
Place 2 trays of ice cubes or a molded ice ring in a large punch bowl.
Pour punch over ice.
Pour in chilled ginger ale.
Yields 25 servings.

title: roommate's hodgepodge(herb lucas)
directions: Brown together beef, garlic, onion and celery, then drain. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mushroom bites
directions: Combine cream cheese, milk, thyme and parsley.
Fill mushroom caps with cheese mixture.
Bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: slender soup
directions: Mix together and cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender.

title: never fail rice pudding
directions: Cook rice, milk and margarine in top of double boiler, stirring occasionally for 1 hour. Stir eggs, sugar, extract and a dash of salt in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Pour hot mixture into egg mixture and stir well.
Place casserole in pan of hot water in oven.
Stir coconut in after 15 minutes at 325°.
Pudding is done when knife comes out clean.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, milk, egg, parsley, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and shortening.
Form into small balls.
Place on broiler rack and broil for 8 minutes.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine in a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat and boil gently for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and beat with mixer for 1 minute.
Store in refrigerator.

title: crock-pot chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix gravy and broth in crockpot until smooth.
Stir in chicken, vegetables and mushrooms.
Cover and cook on low 4 hours. Stir in peas; mix sour cream and flour.
Stir into chicken. Cover and cook on high 20 minutes.
Mix Bisquick and milk until just moistened.
Drop spoonfuls onto chicken mixture.
Cover and cook on high 45 to 50 minutes until dumplings are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Make crisscross, deep vertical cuts in zucchini and slice in thick 1/4-inch slices which will yield quarters.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Sift flour and mix with fruit and nuts.
Mix sugar and butter well and add eggs and flavoring. Add fruit and nuts until mixture is smooth.
Put into a greased tube pan.
Put into a cold oven and bake at 225° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: may's muffins
directions: Mix flour, mayonnaise and milk; stir until smooth.
Spoon into 6 well-greased muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff. Put aside.
Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in a 3-quart pan.
Bring to a boil, 252°, using a candy thermometer, if available.
If not, drop a little of the mixture into cold water.
If it forms a hard ball, it is ready. Remove from heat and begin to pour in a fine stream into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Beat on high speed with electric mixer until mixture holds its shape and loses its gloss.
Add 1 teaspoon of vanilla and walnuts.
Spoon out on waxed paper and let cool (approximately 2 hours).

title: cherry cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Cream the butter and sugar with electric mixer in large mixing bowl until light and fluffy.
Add 1 egg; beat well.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups flour and salt until well blended.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture by spooning lightly in measuring cup; set aside.
Press remaining crust mixture into prepared pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt candy bars with small amount of milk in microwave.
Add Eagle Brand milk; mix well.
Put in 5-quart ice cream freezer and fining filling with milk to full line.
Freeze as usual in your ice cream freezer.

title: frosted cauliflower
directions: Boil whole head of cauliflower for about 20 minutes, or until tender.
Do not overcook.
Take it out of the water and drain it well.
Using two forks to handle it works best.
Place the cauliflower on the center of the serving plate with the stem side down.
If it does not sit straight, you may have to cut the stem some.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard in a cup, and "frost" the cauliflower with the mixture.
Remove the lid from a jar of cheese whiz and microwave it until it is hot.
Pour the cheese whiz over the cauliflower.
Sprinkle top with creole, and Voile!
Serve while hot.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Saute celery and onion in about 2 tablespoons butter in skillet on low heat.

title: oven-fried catfish
directions: Place bread crumbs in a shallow bowl; set aside.
Combine mayonnaise, water and lemon juice.
Stir well.
Dip fish in mayonnaise mixture.
Dredge in bread crumbs.
Place fish on a baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 450° for 17 to 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork. Yields 8 servings (197 calories and 24% fat per serving).

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix ingredients together well. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325 until done approximately 45-50 minutes. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.

title: perfect rice
directions: Cook rice on medium heat.
As rice begins to swell and absorb water, continue to add more water, stirring often.
Sample rice to determine when it is soft and done.
When done, fill pot full with hot water, stirring well.
Strain in colander and serve.

title: pasta lacqua
directions: Cook green beans al dente.
Melt butter over medium heat; do not brown.
Add diced tomatoes and toss.
Add chicken stock and wine.
Let boil.
Add cheese and al dente green beans.
Add salt and pepper.
Toss with fettucine.

title: a man's salad
directions: Boil 1 cup pineapple juice.
Dissolve jello in it while hot; let
cool.	Mix cream cheese, pineapple, chopped pimento, pecans and celery.
Add
to jello.
Stir thoroughly, then fold in whipped cream.
Congeal.
May
be cut in squares and served on lettuce leaf with cherry on top.

title: 5 minute lemon pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and milk in large bowl.
Then pour in lemonade concentrate.
Mix well.
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill for 30 minutes.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream together butter, salt, sugar and eggs.
Add the scalded milk to the creamed mixture, then cool this mix by adding several cups of flour.
Add yeast and enough white flour to make a soft dough.
The dough should rise until double.
Roll out to 1/2-inch.
Cut out and let rise again. Deep-fat fry until brown on each side.
Ice while hot.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water.
Beat cream cheese; add a little of the hot mixture and beat well.
Add Cool Whip and beat.
Add to Jell-O.
Add celery and pineapple.
Chill until set.
Chopped nuts may be added or sprinkled on top.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef and seasonings together (Worcestershire sauce, onion,
salt,
pepper,
oregano, garlic salt and onion salt). Add
uncooked
rice.
In
deep
skillet or large Dutch oven,
put tomato
juice,
sugar
and a little Worcestershire sauce.
Make meat mixture into balls.
Place in sauce and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours on low or simmer.

title: strawberry cheese pie
directions: Note:
Make glaze first so it will have time to cool before you put it on the pie.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Mix milk and pie filling about 1 minute; let stand 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip and chopped toffee.
Spoon into crust. Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Remove from freezer and let stand 10 minutes to soften before serving.

title: baby carrots
directions: Trim stems from carrots.
Combine all ingredients in a small dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: In a bowl, combine first 5 ingredients. Combine milk and egg. Add to salmon mixture. Mix well. Shape into loaf and put into pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: Cook cake in sheet pan.
Cut into squares.
Split squares lengthwise.
Put ice cream in middle.
Pour sauce over it.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream
Crisco,	sugar
and
eggs for one minute at high speed. Add
1 cup flour and beat for one minute.	Add 2 other cups flour
alternately with milk.
Add flavoring and bake at 325° for one hour.
Turn heat up to 350° for 10 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Use tube pan.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute onion, green pepper and clove of garlic.
Saute vegeburger in separate pan until light brown.
Mix all together and add chili powder as desired.
Add tomatoes and cornmeal, still cooking over low heat.
Add olives. Put into buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
