Cook chicken until done, browning on both sides.
Add chicken to sauce.
Spoon sauce over your favorite pasta.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: waikiki balls(lamb)
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture by tablespoon into balls.
Melt shortening in large skillet.
Brown and cook meatballs.
Remove meatballs and keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.
Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Stir in reserved pineapple syrup, vinegar and soy sauce until smooth. Pour into skillet and cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Add warmed meat, pineapple and green pepper; heat again.
Serve with rice.
Makes enough for 6 persons.

title: english toffee
directions: You will need a candy thermometer, medium saucepan, spoon and buttered jelly roll pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together until combined well.
Bake in a pie shell at 350° until a knife comes out clean.

title: good and moist cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread batter as usual and add 1 heaping tablespoonful mayonnaise.
Makes cornbread very moist.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaves until tender.
Remove chicken and chop into cubes.
Place in a large mixing bowl.
Add all remaining ingredients except cheese and bread crumbs.
Mix well.
Put mixture into a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: all-purpose sauce
directions: Bring sauce to a boil.
Good for chicken and spareribs.

title: hash brown cheese potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream, soup, butter, salt, onion and cheese.
Spread on top of potatoes.
Place cornflakes and butter on top.

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Break up breads.
Combine all ingredients except for margarine.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or on high for 2 hours.

title: glazed chicken drumsticks
directions: Place chicken drumsticks in ungreased shallow glass dish. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Heat oven to 375°.
Line broiler pan with aluminum foil.
Place chicken on rack in broiler pan. Brush chicken with remaining sauce.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: orange cake(delicious!)
directions: Cream together sugar and 1/3 cup shortening.
Add eggs and milk.
Dredge raisins and nuts.
Sift together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add rind and juice of 1 orange.
Bake at 350°.
While still warm, drizzle over top the juice of 1 orange and sugar.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Melt margarine and pour over the other ingredients.
Put in pan and bake for 2 hours at 200°, stirring every 20 minutes. Season with celery salt and garlic salt to taste.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Take half of cake and break into pieces and place into a punch bowl. Mix pudding and cake, then add 1 can cherry pie filling, then 1 can crushed pineapple, then 1 (8 ounce) Cool Whip, then half of the coconut. Repeat the steps and then add maraschino cherries on top.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water; add the scalded, cooled milk. Sift 2 1/2 cups flour in bowl; add sugar and salt (if using plain flour).
Cut in shortening.
Add the yeast mixture; beat vigorously until smooth and bubbly.
Add rest of flour, making a firm dough easily handled without sticking.
Mold as desired.
Let stand in a warm place until double in bulk, which should be about 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake in medium oven (400°) for 20 minutes or until brown. Um-Um-m-m-m-m- Good!

title: broccoli with linguine
directions: Cook broccoli in a small amount of boiling salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain and chop.
Cook linguine according to package directions; drain.
Combine linguine, broccoli, mushrooms, half and half and butter. Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off excess fat.
Simmer for 20 minutes the soups, sauces and chilies.
Place 6 1/2 ounce package tortilla chips in casserole.
Pour meat mixture over chips.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: *pastichio 3
directions: Undercook the macaroni. Rinse with hot water to wash away starch.
Add melted butter. Stir to mix. Add beaten eggs and cheese.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease crock-pot.
Combine all the ingredients in large bowl and mix well.
Pour into crock-pot.
Put slices of cheese on top and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook on low heat for 3 hours.

title: simple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening and salt.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over mixture.
Stir and cool.
Beat eggs slightly.
Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Add flour.
Mix all together and refrigerate (up to one week).
Dough will be sticky.
Roll out and cut into shape.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside 1/2 cup crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour melted margarine over crushed cookies and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil together.
Add dry ingredients, then apples
and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with butterscotch morsels and bake 55 to
60 minutes
at
Very
tasty
for
Thanksgiving and Christmas.

title: slow cooker spanish rice
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off fat.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir thoroughly.
Cover and cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.
May be cooked on higher temperature if you are home to stir (about 3 hours).
Serves 6.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese in medium-sized bowl until fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Before serving, top with pie filling.
Garnish each slice with a dollop of whipped topping.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream butter, cheese, and gradually add powdered sugar.
Beat until mixture is light and fluffy, add vanilla.
Mixture makes about 3 cups.

title: waffles
directions: Stir milk and egg yolks into dry ingredients.
Blend in melted shortening.
Lastly, add 2 beaten egg whites.

title: no fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Add salt and sugar.
(I use pastry cutter to mix with.)
Add enough milk to make soft dough.
Roll out between wax paper.
Bake according to filling directions. Makes 2 crusts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in food processor.
Cream margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
In large bowl, mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Blend the 2 mixtures together; layer cookies and mixture in sand bucket starting with cookies and finishing with cookies.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 (8-inch) round cake pans.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except cream cheese frosting.
With mixer at low speed, beat until well mixed, constantly scraping bowl with rubber spatula.
At high speed, beat 4 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
Pour into prepared pans.

title: spinach squish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Allow frozen spinach to thaw. In a colander, squish out as much water from the spinach as possible. Set aside.

title: parmesan peas
directions: Cook peas as directed on package.
Drain.
Toss with remaining ingredients.
Serve with additional grated Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: honey oat loaf(no knead)
directions: In large bowl mix together water and honey; sprinkle in yeast and let stand 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except for flour.
With rubber spatula gradually work in flour.
Mixture will be thick.
Let rise for 30 minutes in warm place.
Work with spatula again and let rise until double in bulk, about 75 minutes. Turn onto floured board, cut in half and pat each half into loaf shape.
Dough will be very soft.
Using 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) pans, pour 1 tablespoon oil into each.
Drop each loaf into a pan and turn to oil the top.
Let rise until 1/2 inch from top of pan.
Place in cold oven with shallow pan of water on bottom of oven.
Set oven for 350° and bake 45 minutes.
Turn out gently as bread will be very soft.

title: ethel's banana pudding
directions: Mix
pudding
with
milk, adding sour cream and half of the Cool
Whip.
Slice	bananas
over
vanilla	wafers.
Pour pudding mixture
over
bananas and ice with rest of Cool Whip. Store in refrigerator for 2 hours to set before slicing.
The only place
I could find French vanilla pudding was at Kroger. It is not the same with a substitute.

title: cheese onion bread
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender. Combine eggs, milk, Bisquick and 2/3 cup cheese in bowl, mixing well. Add onion, stirring to blend. Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Mix remaining 2 tablespoons butter, 1/3 cup cheese and poppy seed. Sprinkle topping over batter. Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes or until loaf tests done.

title: no salt seasoning mix
directions: Mix all spices together.
Store in airtight jar.
Use to spice up dishes without using salt.

title: sad brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: soccer squares
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup until bubbly; stir often.
Remove from heat, stir in peanut butter and cereal.
Mix well.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together in a pot over medium heat stirring.
Spread over cereal mixture and refrigerate one hour.
Cut in squares. Makes 24.

title: hobo meal
directions: Patty hamburger meat.
Place in foil.
Layer veggies on top. Top with butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Seal tightly.
Bake over open fire or in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until done. Over fire, turn after 15 minutes and cook 15 minutes more.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add 1/2 of the condensed milk and blend.
Pour 1/2 batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt and blend caramels and remaining milk.
Spread over baked cake. Sprinkle with pecans.
Cover with remaining batter and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: freezer coleslaw
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, water and celery to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil 1 minute.
Cool to room temperature.
In a large bowl, toss together cabbage and remaining ingredients.
Set aside.
Drain cabbage mixture.
Stir cooled vinegar mixture into cabbage mixture until well mixed.
Pack coleslaw in three one-pint freezer safe containers.
Leave 1/2-inch space on top.
Cover and freeze.
Store in freezer up to 6 months.
Thaw coleslaw about 3 hours at room temperature before serving.
Makes 3 pints.

title: spinach soup
directions: Brown onions in butter.
Add 46 ounce can chicken broth. bring to boil, add 2 cups Coffee-mate, potatoes, carrots and rice. Simmer 15 minutes.
Add 10 ounce package chopped spinach, 1 package asparagus or can asparagus and 1 tablespoon bouillon (instant).
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: peach delight
directions: Mix melted margarine, 1 cup flour and chopped pecans.
Press in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: pickled beets
directions: Mix sugar, water and vinegar; cook on medium heat.
Add salt and beets; simmer for a few minutes, then put in sterile jar.
May increase for large canning.

title: shrimp and cucumber salad
directions: Mix Ranch dressing, lemon juice and dill.
Stir until blended well. Add remaining ingredients.
Serve.

title: chicken divine
directions: Layer broccoli on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Place chicken on top.
Mix together the next 3 ingredients and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Add cheese and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes; do not cover.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mustard fried catfish
directions: Brush fillets lightly with half of mustard.
Place cornmeal, salt, red pepper and pepper in a zip-top plastic bag; drop in fillets, one at a time, and shake until completely coated.
Brush fillets with remaining mustard; return to bag and shake again.
Fry in deep hot oil (350°) 4 to 5 minutes or until catfish fillets float to the top and are golden brown; drain well.
Transfer fillets to a serving platter; garnish with parsley and lemon wedges.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 servings.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Beat the pulp, soda, sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly. Sift together the flour, spices and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture and beat well.
Stir nuts and raisins into the mixture. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until slightly brown (about 15 minutes).
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: ranch corn
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in an 8 to 9-inch square pan. Sprinkle with cheese, mixing a little in as you go.
Turn oven to 350°.
Bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: marinade for beef roast
directions: Marinate roast overnight.
Remove 1/2 the sauce and freeze. Cook roast at 325° until done, basting often.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Cook noodles.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Line with noodles. Beat egg with milk; pour over noodles.
Mix hamburger, soup and pizza sauce; spread over noodles.
Add other spices and toppings; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese and butter get to room temperature.
Grate cheese and mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Shape cheese into 1 large or 2 small balls.
Roll in crushed nuts and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: icebox slaw
directions: In saucepan, bring to a boil the last 5 ingredients and pour over the vegetables.
Cover tightly and put in refrigerator.
This keeps for several days.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: To make sour milk, mix 1 cup milk with 2 tablespoons vinegar.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients except for the topping.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Add crumbs and butter on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes until brown.
Yield:
5 servings.

title: ham and barley soup
directions: About 2 1/2 hours before serving, cut celery into 1/4-inch slices.
Cut carrots into 1 1/2 x 1/2-inch pieces.
Dice onions. Peel and cut turnips into 1/2-inch chunks; thickly slice mushrooms.

title: water chestnut appetizer
directions: Mix together and heat first 3 ingredients.
Leave heated in fondue pot.
Wrap water chestnuts in bacon and secure with toothpick.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 350° for approximately 20 minutes or until bacon is done.
Dip bacon pieces in sauce.

title: cheese crunchies
directions: Mix cheese and margarine (room temperature); add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls and flatten with fork on baking sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add flour and butter and mix well.
Add buttermilk and flavoring.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until set.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Rinse and chop finely the dried beef.
Combine 1/4 cup dried beef with cream cheese, sour cream, grated Parmesan cheese and horseradish.
Blend thoroughly.
Refrigerate mixture for 15 minutes.
Form into ball and roll into remaining beef; chill. Serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In medium mixing bowl, beat eggs, sugar, peanut butter, corn syrup and vanilla at medium speed until blended. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until crust is brown and filling is puffy, about 50 to 60 minutes. Cool on wire rack before cutting. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: gram's raisin cake(100 year old recipe)
directions: Mix
sugar
and
cocoa;
add
water, butter, spices and salt. Boil 4 minutes;
cool.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and
soda.	Add
to
raisin mixture and mix until well blended. Stir
in
walnuts.	Pour
into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Can be stored in freezer up to 6 months.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into 2 pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until set up; about 40 minutes to 1 hour.

title: bunny nest
directions: Melt margarine on low heat.
Remove from heat; add sugar and coconut.
Mix well.
Add food coloring.

title: grilled salmon steaks
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into glass pan.
Add 1 tablespoon of water.
Add fish.
Turn to coat with marinade. Cover and marinate at room temperature for 30 minutes or in refrigerator for 2 hours, turning steaks occasionally.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine chicken and vegetables in a greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Set aside.
Stir flour, salt and pepper into butter. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until bubbly.
Gradually add broth, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Top with corn meal pastry or pie crust.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until it falls off bone.
Skin and debone it. Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, mix both cans soup and picante.
Mix well and add cheese until it is melted.
Crunch up handful of chips and set aside.
Now crunch 1/2 bag of chips and put in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan, then layer 1/2 of chicken on top and then 1/2 of cheese sauce on top.
Then repeat with other 1/2 in same order.
Sprinkle top with chips and Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef stew
directions: On waxed paper, coat stew meat with flour; reserve leftover flour.
In a 6-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook meat, a few pieces at a time, until well browned on all sides, removing pieces as they brown.
Reduce heat to medium.
To drippings in Dutch oven, add chopped onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is almost tender, about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in reserved flour until blended.
Gradually stir in 3 cups water, bouillon, salt, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is slightly thickened.
Add meat and heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer about 2 1/2 hours or until meat is almost tender, stirring occasionally.
Add potatoes and carrot chunks.
Over medium heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Stir in frozen peas.
Cover and simmer 5 to 10 minutes until all vegetables are tender.
Serve with dumplings or noodles. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain fat.
Add 1 tablepsoon parsley, 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, tomato paste, 1 tablespoon basil, tomatoes and chopped garlic clove.
Simmer until thick (about 45 to 60 minutes).
Cook noodles until tender, drain and rinse in cold water.
Combine cottage cheese, eggs, 2 tablespoon parsley, pepper and Parmesan cheese; mix well.
Place half of cooked noodles in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and spread half of cheese mixture over noodles.
Add half of grated Mozzarella and half of meat sauce; repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes and cut into squares.
Enjoy!

title: sun-maid raisin nut cake(our family christmas cake since 1936)
directions: Cream butter with brown sugar.
Add molasses, beaten eggs and buttermilk, in which the soda has been dissolved.
Mix and sift the flour, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to this dry mixture the Sun-Maid raisins (cut in pieces) and walnuts (coarsely chopped).
Combine dry ingredients with the first mixture.
Bake in 3 layers in moderate oven at 350° for about 25 minutes.
When cool, cover with your favorite icing.
I use Caramel Icing.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and flour.
Mix egg yolks, sugar and baking powder.
Beat egg whites stiff; save to last.
Add to mixture fresh coconut (grated), red and green cherries, red and green pineapple, white raisins and nuts.
Add juice of fresh orange; add egg whites.
Bake in 275° oven for 30 minutes per pound.

title: spinach new orleans
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well. Add cream cheese and 1/2 stick butter.
Mix well.
Melt second 1/2 stick butter.
Mix with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle mixture on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown beef.
Add onion, garlic, celery and bell peppers.
Add rest of ingredients and cook for 2 hours.
Add spaghetti sauce mix.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and hot water.
Bring to a boil and boil 2 minutes.
Add milk and heat almost to boiling.
Serve.

title: beef and cheese foldover(one dish meals)
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir in barbecue sauce; set aside.
Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll crescent dough into 4 long rectangles on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Overlap long sides; firmly press perforations and edges to seal.
Pat to form 15 x 13-inch rectangle.
Spread meat mixture lengthwise in a 4-inch wide strip, down center of dough to within 1-inch of ends.
Top meat with cheese slices.
Fold shorter sides of dough 1-inch over filling.
Bring long sides of dough rectangle over filling, overlapping edges; pinch edge to seal.
Sprinkle with sesame seed. Bake at 375 ° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: pizza piena - easter meat pie
directions: *To cut down calories, heavily grease pan and dust with flour. Works out well.

title: cantaloupe soup(the blender at its best)
directions: Remove seeds from cantaloupe and cube the pulp.
Place pulp and cinnamon in electric blender and puree.
Combine orange and lime juices and stir into the puree.
Chill and serve in chilled soup bowls.
Garnish with mint sprigs.
Serves 5.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Combine ginger ale, orange juice
and marshmallows and melt over low heat. Cool.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Combine juice, egg yolk, flour, sugar and butter; cook until thick.
After cool, add Cool Whip.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over crackers.
Put on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.
Stir every 5 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Fry bacon crisp and crumble over shredded cabbage.
Add chopped onion and combine dressing ingredients which can be thinned with milk, if desired.
Add to salad.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In a bowl, mix well the cottage cheese, eggs, onion, broccoli and cornbread mix.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place a layer of bread crumbs, asparagus and soup in casserole dish. Top with layer of bread crumbs. Dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 2-minute fudge
directions: In 1 1/2 quart casserole, stir together sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla until partially blended.
Put butter or margarine over top in center of dish.
Microwave on High 2 minutes.
Stir well until smooth.
Pour into greased 8-inch square dish.
Chill 1 hour.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken pieces, soups, pimentos and seasonings in saucepan.
Heat until bubbling and hot.
Line a large Pyrex casserole dish (that has been sprayed with Pam) with chow mein noodles.
Pour hot chicken/soup mixture over noodles.
Top with grated cheese.
Place in 350° oven until cheese is golden brown.

title: pork tenderloin
directions: Cut tenderloin into 8 pieces; place each piece between 2 pieces of plastic wrap or waxed paper and flatten to 1/2-inch thickness.
Sprinkle with lemon pepper.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Cook pork for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until no longer pink and juices run clear.
Remove to a serving platter and keep warm.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Combine pretzels, butter and 1/4 cup sugar.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup sugar together.
Spread over pretzel mixture. Next, put a generous layer of Cool Whip.
Dissolve Jell-O mix in heated pineapple juice.
Remove from heat; let partially set.
Add strawberries.
Spread over mixture and refrigerate until Jell-O is firm.
Top with Cool Whip and crushed pretzels.

title: quick southwestern pizza
directions: Move oven rack to lowest position.
Heat oven to 450°.
Grease cookie sheet or 12-inch pizza pan.
Mix baking mix and water. Beat vigorously 20 strokes.
Turn onto floured surface.
Knead about 60 times or until no longer sticky.
Press into 13-inch circle on cookie sheet; pinch edge, forming 1/2-inch rim, or press in pizza pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook about 1/2 hour until slightly thickened.
Flavor should be "sweet and sour".

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten the chicken breasts with wooden mallet and season with salt and pepper.
Roll the strips of cheese in the ham slices and place in the center of the flattened breast.
Fold the edges over one another and press tightly.
Dredge them with flour and dip into beaten eggs.
Coat well with bread crumbs.
Chill until ready to fry.
Cook at 325° in deep fat for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: rainbow sherbet squares
directions: Any desired combinations of sherbets can be used.
Combine whipped cream, sugar, cookies and nuts.
Spread about 1/3 of mixture into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon sherbet over this layer. It is easier to do if the sherbet is fairly soft.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Fold in sour cream and mix well.
Pour into preheated greased iron skillet and bake until golden brown.

title: doo dads
directions: In large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over all dry ingredients.
Bake at 225° for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put sugar and milk in pan and cook until small ball forms in cold water.
Take off fire; add peanut butter, vanilla and butter. Beat until thick and pour into two buttered plates.

title: bible cake("behold there was a cake baken." 1 kings 19:6)
directions: Grease and flour a 9 1/2-inch tube pan.
Chop nuts and fruit fine; flour well with flour from the 2 cups.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry; set aside.
In mixing bowl, blend butter, sugar, spices and salt.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Sift in baking powder and flour; add water and honey.
Stir in floured nuts and fruits; beat.
Fold into well beaten mixture the egg whites.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 30 to 60 minutes at 375°.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: In saucepan on very low heat, mix butter, heavy cream, parsley, sherry and garlic powder until smooth.
Add egg yolks. Remove from heat and pour over fettucini.
Top with Parmesan.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan by package directions, adding 1 teaspoon of flavoring and 1 package of frozen coconut. Mix together powdered sugar, milk and water.
Pour over cake immediately after taking from the oven.
Allow cake to cool. Spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle other package of coconut. Sprinkle with pecans.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Put in large airtight bowl. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thickness on floured surface.
Use cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° until golden brown. May use icing and sprinkles when cooled.

title: crock-pot deer chili
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil in skillet.
Add onions and stir in chili pepper.
Transfer into crock-pot.
Stir in tomatoes and beans.
Cook on low all day.
Yummy!

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, cream of tartar and salt into mixing bowl.
Drop in shortening and add 2/3 of milk, then vanilla and beat.
Add eggs and beat.
Add the remaining 1/3 of milk and beat.
Bake at 350°.

title: minnie's famous pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and egg whites; slowly add flour and sour cream.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Mix and pour into stem cake pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Press cracker crumbs with 1 stick melted margarine into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Set aside.

title: pizza puff
directions: In skillet cook meat on medium-high heat until browned, adding oil as needed.
Drain off all but 2 teaspoons fat.
Add vegetables, saute until limp.
Add sauce and seasonings.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes.
Spread meat mix in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish/pan.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over meat.
In blender add eggs, milk, flour, 1 tablespoon oil and salt.
Blend, pour over cheese. Sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until browned and puffy, about 30 minutes.

title: delicious chicken casserole
directions: Mix all together (except eggs) and put 1/2 of mixture in bottom of casserole dish.
Slice all the eggs.
Use as the middle layer and then add the rest of mixture on top of this.
Top with a cup of crushed cornflakes and 1 stick of butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: ramen noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles for 3 minutes and break into small pieces.
Chop or grate cabbage.
Mix drained noodles, cabbage, nuts, chicken and peas in a large bowl.
Mix flavor packages, oil, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over cabbage mixture and blend together.
Top with sunflower seeds and chill.
Makes a lot.

title: tabooley-lebanese parsley salad
directions: Rinse wheat in water until water is no longer cloudy.
Soak for 5 minutes.
Squeeze dry by cupping hands and pressing between palms of hands.
Use food processor to pulsate parsley to save time or chop fine on cutting board.
Chop onions, mint leaves and tomatoes very fine.
Place vegetables in a large bowl; add wheat, lemon juice, oil, salt and pepper and mix well.
Serve with fresh small grape leaves or place salad on romaine lettuce leaves used as scoops.
Serves 6.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter.
Stir in egg yolks.
Gradually add 3 cups flour; mix well.
Roll into small balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Dip finger in water and make shallow depression in each ball of dough.
Put a bit of jelly (color of your choice) in each depression.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
(This is a good recipe to make when also making Forgotten Cookies, as the remaining egg yolks are used.)

title: ida ceconi's vienna cookies
directions: Work flour and shortening together, then work in sugar to a crumbly mixture.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Pinch off small amounts of this dough so that when it is rolled, it is about the size of a small walnut.
After it is rolled between the hands, flatten slightly to about 3/4 of an inch thick.
Make a small indentation in the center with finger large enough to hold a small amount of tart jelly.
Brush each cookie with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with finely chopped nutmeats and sugar.
Put in refrigerator for about 1 hour.
Bake in slow oven (250°) for 20 minutes, then gradually increase heat to 300° and bake about 40 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix soups, Ro-Tel and milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and pour into casserole dish.
Add crumbled tortilla chips and diced chicken; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Remove from oven and add grated cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes more, uncovered, or until cheese melts.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mash cranberry sauce and add lemon juice and blend.
Pour into a 1-quart refrigerator tray or 1 (9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pan. Soften cream cheese.
Add sugar and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Add pecans and whipped cream.
Spoon cheese mixture over cranberries. Freeze until firm.
To serve, cut into slices and serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 servings.

title: apple or banana pancakes
directions: I use pancake mix, the dry bought kind.
Chop apples real fine and mix into mixture.
You will not need to add the full amount of water.
Cook as usual.
If you add bananas, mash real good and remember to put less water in mixture.

title: grape sparkle
directions: Heat 1 cup of the grape juice just to boiling point.
Add the gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add other cup of grape juice (ice cubes may be added for quick cooling).
Wash and let grapes dry.
Place grapes in the bottom of a bowl or in individual dessert glasses.
Pour thickened gelatin mixture over the grapes.
Chill until firm.
Yields 4 servings.

title: pecan caramel candy
directions: Melt 1 cup sugar and corn syrup.
Add milk, then add rest of sugar.
Cook on low temperature until it forms firm ball (245° on thermometer).
Add vanilla, butter and nuts.
Pour on buttered wax paper or foil.

title: chinese spareribs (barbecue)
directions: Cut spareribs into 2-inch sections.
Place in large bowl, add remaining ingredients.
Mix with spareribs and marinate for 6 hours.
Cook in 300° oven in the marinade sauce until tender.
Add some water when needed.
Brown under broiler flame.
Garnish with sweet and sour sauce (Duck Sauce or Saucy Susan).
Serves 4 to 6.

title: stuffed rolls
directions: Mix all of the
ingredients
together.
Slice rolls and remove some of the center from
the rolls to make room for the filling (save and freeze for
later
use
when
you need bread crumbs). Fill each
roll
with
approximately
tablespoons filling (more or less,
depending
on
size
of
rolls).
Wrap individually in foil and
refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.
Then place on cookie
sheet
and heat thoroughly in 300° oven until hot through (about
to 30 minutes, depending on whether or not they are frozen).
Serve with salad and dessert for a light meal. Leftovers can be reheated.

title: cranberry gelatin salad
directions: Grind together the cranberries, orange and apples.
Add the pineapple juice to the gelatin and hot water.
Mix other ingredients together and allow to set in refrigerator until solid.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix bean, onion and pepper together in bowl. Mix the vinegar, oil and sugar together and mix with beans. Let set overnight before serving.

title: french silk pie
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Line a greased glass pie plate.
(This is crust.)

title: crab quiche
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in remainder of ingredients. Pour in shell.
Bake in 300° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until custard is set and knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve hot. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time and beat well. Add milk alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Add grated rind or lemon.
Bake in loaf pan 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix sugar and juice of 1 lemon and pour over bread.
Let stand 1/2 hour then remove from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Simmer all ingredients for 15 minutes on medium.

title: zebra cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, cocoa, cinnamon, baking powder and salt. Cover.
Refrigerate for 2 hours or longer.
Lightly grease baking sheet; set aside.
Place confectioners sugar in a small bowl. Shape dough in 1-inch balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 minutes. Cool on rack.

title: instant miracle rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside. In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar and baking soda.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast, mixing well.
Cover dough and chill 2 hours. Place dough on a floured cloth.
Roll out and cut with a biscuit cutter.
Place in pan and set aside until dough reaches room temperature. Brush with melted butter and bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes 36 rolls.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in one 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: asparagus - english pea casserole
directions: Dilute soup with juice from peas to make 1 can.
Layer in casserole dish.
Cover with soup.
Top with salt and pepper, butter and cheese.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and serve over or with fruit.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients (except pie shell) together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: mom's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, butter and vanilla. Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring often.
Pour into pie shells.
Top with whipped cream.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Place 9 bread slices in a single layer on bottom of slightly greased 13 x 9 pan.
Top with cream cheese slices.
Place remaining bread slices on top.
Whisk together eggs, milk, syrup and cinnamon.
Pour over bread.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Lightly cover with foil after 20 minutes.

title: jiffy plum cake
directions: Mix all except nuts in large bowl.
Beat well.
Add pecans and stir.
Bake 50 or 60 minutes at 350°.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain meat. Add all other ingredients and simmer for 1 1/2 hours. Serve over fritos with sour cream and grated cheese.

title: german christmas butter cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar until creamy.
Add one whole egg and 2 yolks and the juice of lemon.
Sift flour and baking powder; add butter mix.
Roll between two pieces of wax paper quite thin. Stamp out shapes.
Mix a little cold water with egg whites and blend with fork.
Brush on cookies.
Decorate cookies with nuts, colored sugar, etc.
Bake approximately 15 minutes at 350°.

title: breaded herbed fish fillets
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients.
Coat fillets with cooking spray; dredge in breadcrumb mixture.
Place fillets on a broiler pan coated with cooking spray; bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve immediately.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cheese and bacon puffs
directions: Pat rounded teaspoonful of filling on crackers.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Broil under broiler until bubbly and lightly brown. Serve at once.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Grease a cookie sheet.
Beat egg whites, vanilla and salt until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in coconut.
Drop from a teaspoon 1 1/2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for about 20 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Makes about 20 to 24.

title: ham noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles in
boiling,
unsalted water until tender. Drain. In a large bowl
stir together the soup, milk and sour cream. Add celery,
mushrooms, pimiento and parsley.
Stir in cooked noodles
and ham;
turn
into
a
quart
casserole. Combine cracker crumbs and melted butter and sprinkle over the casserole. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.

title: pork chops and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in shortening; remove from skillet and season.
Pour off some of the drippings.
Add rice, green pepper, onions, chicken broth and thyme; stir.
Place pork chops on top. Cover and cook in frypan at 275° for 30 minutes or pour into a 3-quart casserole and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Serves 6.
